cs.CR, cs.DS, cs.DB, cs.LG, cs.IT 

The paper addresses the problem of privacy preservation in social platforms, which is a common concern in the field of computer security (cs.CR). The framework of differential privacy is applied to rank aggregation, which involves algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) as well as databases (cs.DB). The paper also analyzes the error probability of the aggregated ranking, which is related to machine learning and data analysis (cs.LG) as well as information theory (cs.IT).
